            <title>[SOLR-160] [Patch] Get Test Solr Server working in Windows environment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-160</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Because Windows does not support forking processes I created a patch that uses the Win32 api to create and destroy a process to control the test solr server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached two files: 1) the patch and 2) the results from running &apos;rake test&apos;  In my environment I have two failures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My approach was to still support the including/requiring of the single file test/functional/test_solr_server.rb and have it further require the platform dependent start/stop api.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
